= 9.1 Neural Control of Involuntary Effectors

== Autonomic Neurons

- The *autonomic nervous system* (ANS, 自主神经系统) regulates *cardiac muscle* (心肌), *smooth muscles* (平滑肌), and *glands* (腺体), which are *involuntary effectors* (非随意效应器).
- Autonomic motor control involves a *two-neuron pathway* (双神经元通路):
  - *Preganglionic neuron* (节前神经元): Cell body in the CNS (brain or spinal cord), axon synapses in an *autonomic ganglion* (自主神经节).
  - *Postganglionic neuron* (节后神经元): Cell body in the autonomic ganglion, axon extends to and synapses with the effector organ.
  - #figure(
      image(images.at("9-1").path, width: 50%),
    )
- This contrasts with *somatic motor neurons* (躯体运动神经元), which have a single neuron from CNS directly to skeletal muscle.
- *Comparison of somatic and autonomic motor systems*:
  - Somatic: one neuron, no ganglia, innervates skeletal muscles, always excitatory, uses acetylcholine.
  - Autonomic: two neurons, has ganglia, innervates cardiac muscle/smooth muscle/glands, can be excitatory or inhibitory.
  - #figure(
      image(images.at("table-9-1").path, width: 70%),
    )
- Preganglionic fibers originate in midbrain, hindbrain, and thoracic to sacral spinal cord levels.
- Autonomic ganglia are located in the head, neck, abdomen, and in chains parallel to the spinal cord.

== Visceral Effector Organs

- *Visceral effector organs* (内脏效应器) include organs within body cavities and blood vessels.
- Unlike skeletal muscles, visceral effectors maintain function after *denervation* (去神经):
  - Smooth muscles maintain *resting tone* (静息张力) without nerve stimulation.
  - *Denervation hypersensitivity* (去神经超敏): Target tissue becomes more sensitive to stimulating agents after nerve damage.
- *Cardiac muscle* (心肌) and many *smooth muscles* (平滑肌) exhibit *intrinsic rhythmicity* (内在节律性): they contract rhythmically without nerve stimulation.
- Autonomic innervation modulates this intrinsic activity by increasing or decreasing it.
- Autonomic nerves maintain *resting tone* (baseline firing rate) that can be increased or decreased.
- Some autonomic neurotransmitters are *inhibitory* (抑制性), unlike somatic motor neurons which are always excitatory.

= 9.2 Divisions of the Autonomic Nervous System

== Sympathetic Division

- The *sympathetic division* (交感神经分部) is also called the *thoracolumbar division* (胸腰分部) because preganglionic fibers originate from *T1 to L2* spinal levels.
- Preganglionic fibers exit via ventral roots and synapse in:
  - *Paravertebral ganglia* (椎旁神经节): A double chain of ganglia (the *sympathetic chain*, 交感链) running parallel to the spinal cord on both sides.
  - #figure(
      image(images.at("9-2").path, width: 50%),
    )
- *White rami communicantes* (白交通支): Myelinated preganglionic axons diverge from spinal nerves to enter the sympathetic chain.
- *Gray rami communicantes* (灰交通支): Unmyelinated postganglionic axons return from ganglia to spinal nerves.
- Pathway variations:
  - Some preganglionic fibers synapse in the sympathetic chain; postganglionic fibers rejoin spinal nerves via gray rami.
  - Others pass through the chain without synapsing, forming *splanchnic nerves* (内脏神经) that synapse in *collateral ganglia* (副神经节).
  - #figure(
      image(images.at("9-3").path, width: 50%),
    )
- *Collateral ganglia* (副神经节) include:
  - *Celiac ganglion* (腹腔神经节)
  - *Superior mesenteric ganglion* (肠系膜上神经节)
  - *Inferior mesenteric ganglion* (肠系膜下神经节)
  - These are unpaired, located in the abdominal cavity.
  - #figure(
      image(images.at("9-4").path, width: 50%),
    )
- *Divergence* (发散): One preganglionic fiber synapses with multiple postganglionic neurons in different ganglia.
- *Convergence* (汇聚): One postganglionic neuron receives input from multiple preganglionic fibers.
- This organization results in *mass activation* (大规模激活) of the sympathetic system, affecting all effector organs simultaneously.
- #figure(
    image(images.at("table-9-2").path, width: 70%),
  )

=== Adrenal Glands

- The *adrenal medulla* (肾上腺髓质) is a modified sympathetic ganglion.
- Preganglionic sympathetic fibers directly innervate adrenal medulla cells (modified postganglionic neurons).
- Upon stimulation, adrenal medulla secretes *catecholamines* (儿茶酚胺) into the bloodstream:
  - *Epinephrine* (肾上腺素, adrenaline): 85%
  - *Norepinephrine* (去甲肾上腺素, noradrenaline): 15%
- These hormones have effects similar to sympathetic nerve stimulation but are longer-lasting.
- The sympathoadrenal system provides the *fight-or-flight response* (战斗或逃跑反应).

== Parasympathetic Division

- The *parasympathetic division* (副交感神经分部) is also called the *craniosacral division* (颅骶分部).
- Preganglionic fibers originate from:
  - *Cranial nerves* (脑神经): III (oculomotor, 动眼神经), VII (facial, 面神经), IX (glossopharyngeal, 舌咽神经), and X (vagus, 迷走神经).
  - *Sacral spinal cord* (骶髓): S2 to S4.
- Parasympathetic ganglia are *terminal ganglia* (终末神经节) located near or within target organs.
- Preganglionic fibers are long; postganglionic fibers are short.
- #figure(
    image(images.at("table-9-3").path, width: 70%),
  )

=== Cranial Parasympathetic Nerves

- *Oculomotor nerve (III)*: Synapses in *ciliary ganglion* (睫状神经节), innervates ciliary muscle and iris constrictor muscles of the eye.
- *Facial nerve (VII)*: 
  - Synapses in *pterygopalatine ganglion* (翼腭神经节), innervates lacrimal glands, nasal mucosa, pharynx, palate.
  - Synapses in *submandibular ganglion* (下颌下神经节), innervates submandibular and sublingual salivary glands.
- *Glossopharyngeal nerve (IX)*: Synapses in *otic ganglion* (耳神经节), innervates parotid salivary gland.
- *Vagus nerve (X)*: The most extensive parasympathetic nerve.
  - Preganglionic fibers travel through neck, thorax, and abdomen.
  - Synapses in terminal ganglia within target organs.
  - Innervates heart, lungs, esophagus, stomach, pancreas, liver, small intestine, and upper half of large intestine.

=== Overview of Both Divisions

- Most parasympathetic fibers do not travel in spinal nerves (unlike sympathetic fibers).
- Therefore, *cutaneous effectors* (皮肤效应器) like blood vessels, sweat glands, and arrector pili muscles receive only sympathetic innervation.
- #figure(
    image(images.at("9-5").path, width: 60%),
  )

=== Sacral Parasympathetic Nerves

- Preganglionic fibers from S2-S4 form *pelvic nerves* (盆神经).
- Innervate lower half of large intestine, rectum, urinary bladder, and reproductive organs.
- Synapse in terminal ganglia within the organs.
- #figure(
    image(images.at("9-6").path, width: 50%),
  )

